The paper discusses the development of proactive chatbots for business process automation, which involves the use of artificial intelligence and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also emphasizes the importance of user-friendly interfaces, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of natural language processing also suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the orchestration of multiple agents, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of chatbots on various domains, including banking and insurance, which suggests cs.CY (Computers and Society) as a possible sub-category.
